cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CE

This paper deals with the problem of inferring node mobility based on wireless contact traces, which is a common problem in the field of computer networks and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a heuristic algorithm inspired by graph drawing, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on both synthetic and real-life contact traces, which could fall under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of simulating protocols in dense networks, which could fall under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
